    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Removal - Front Crankcase Cover
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.2.9" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Front Crankcase Cover</title>
        <figure id="f3450009023" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="532px"
                     scalefitheight="408px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front crankcase cover bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 75 bolt (7)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 45 bolt (10)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device and get help when removing,
                    lowering, and installing the front cover.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not remove four M8&#160;x&#160;25 oil pump housing assembly bolts at this time. Damage to oil
                    pump may result.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Support front cover while removing bolts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove seven M8&#160;x&#160;75 bolts and 10 M8&#160;x&#160;45 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, cut protruding sealant from the joint of the crankcase and lower
                    crankcase before removing the front cover gasket. If the sealant is not cut, the seal between the
                    crankcase and lower crankcase may fail. Complete engine removal and disassembly is required to
                    install a new crankcase gasket.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove front crankcase cover and discard gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009024" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0605A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Sealant between crankcase and lower crankcase joint</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a thin blade scraper to cut sealant where crankcase and lower crankcase meet.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
